elta\\ln n$, $r(K_p(1,a,b,\\dots,b), B_{k,n})=\n(p-1)(n-1)+k(p-1)(a-1)+1$ if $a|(n-1-k)$, where the case when $a=1$ has been\nproved by Nikiforov and Rousseau (2009) using the regularity lemma. The bounds\non $1/\\delta$ we obtain are not of tower-type since our proofs do not rely on\nthe regularity lemma.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Apr 2022 14:17:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-08"}
